Plan: Transit Reference Strategy & Build Process Overhaul
Context
We've been hitting Transit encoding failures ("Tried to deserialize Record type named 'undefined'") because:

Cache keys are positional, not stable. The components example file uses ^16=uuid, ^18=type, ^19=subtype. But the Samsara build scripts hardcode ^19=uuid, ^1;=type, ^1<=subtype. These differ because Transit assigns cache numbers based on order of first appearance in the serialized output. Every exported file can have different cache key assignments.

RETOOL_JSON_REFERENCE.md documents the wrong cache keys — it documents the Samsara/hotel-search lineage keys, which don't match the components example file or any other independently exported app.

String concatenation with hardcoded cache refs is inherently fragile — the generate_samsara_app.py approach breaks whenever the base file changes.

Good news: The Tiller dashboard script (apps/tiller retool dashboard/generate_app.py) already solved this by using full field names (uuid, type, subtype, etc.) instead of cache refs. Retool's Transit reader handles both formats. This approach is immune to cache key drift.

Also good news: The components example file already has 177 plugins across 102 widget subtypes — it IS a comprehensive kitchen sink app. The gaps are in queries/patterns, not widgets.

Part 1: Enhance the Kitchen Sink App in Retool
The components example covers 102 widget subtypes but is thin on queries, state, and event patterns. Add these to the app in Retool, then re-export:

Add to the app:

 2-3 state variables (persistence: none, localStorage, urlHash)
 A SQL query (RetoolTableQuery against Retool DB)
 A REST query with headers and URL params
 A JavaScript transformer that processes query data
 A form with submit handler that triggers a query + shows success notification
 An event handler chain: button click -> run query -> onSuccess set variable + show modal
 A second page with navigation between pages
 A table with action column (edit/delete buttons per row)
After adding, export and replace apps/general references/components exmple.json.

Re-export cadence: Only when:

A Retool version update changes Transit format (check changelog quarterly)
You need a widget type not currently in the file
An import fails with a new error pattern
No need for weekly re-exports — Transit format changes are rare.

Part 2: Create Shared Builder Library
Extract the Tiller script's helpers into a reusable module.

File: tools/retool_builder.py

Source: [generate_app.py](apps/tiller retool dashboard/generate_app.py) lines 27-200

Functions to extract:

tmap(*args) — Transit map ["^ ", k1, v1, ...]
tom(*args) — Transit ordered map ["~#iOM", [...]]
tlist(items) — Transit list ["~#iL", [...]]
record(name, value) — Transit record ["~#iR", ...]
pos(row, col, height, width, container, screen) — Position builder
widget(id, subtype, template, position, ...) — Widget plugin
query(id, subtype, template, resource, ...) — Query plugin
state_var(id, value, persistence) — State variable plugin
screen_plugin(id, title, slug, order) — Screen plugin
frame_plugin(id, screen, frame_type) — Frame plugin
build_app(plugins, app_config) — Assemble full appState from plugin list
save_app(app_state, output_path, app_name) — Wrap in outer JSON + write
Add new convenience builders:

evt_trigger_query(query_id) — Event handler that triggers a query
evt_show_frame(frame_id) — Event handler to show modal/drawer
evt_set_var(var_id, value) — Event handler to set a state variable
evt_chain(events) — Chain multiple event handlers
table_columns(col_defs) — Build _columnIds + column maps from a simple list of {key, title, format, ...} dicts
notification(type, title, description) — Success/error notification
Usage pattern for new apps:

from tools.retool_builder import *

plugins = [
    screen_plugin("page1", "Dashboard", "dashboard", 0),
    frame_plugin("$main", "page1", "main"),
    widget("title", "TextWidget2", tom("value", "# Dashboard", "heightType", "auto"),
           pos(0, 0, 4, 12, "$main", "page1"), screen="page1"),
    query("fetchData", "RESTQuery", tom(...), resource_uuid="...", screen="page1"),
]
app = build_app(plugins)
save_app(app, "apps/my-app/my-app.json", "My App")
Part 3: Transit Pattern Extraction Script
File: tools/extract_transit_patterns.py

Parses the components example file and outputs a structured reference of every widget template, query template, and event handler pattern found.

What it extracts:

Cache key resolution map for this specific file (for documentation only)
Widget templates by subtype — the full template ordered map for each of the 102 subtypes, with keys decoded to full field names
Query templates by subtype — same for the 2 query types present
Event handler patterns — all unique event handler structures found
Position examples — how different widget types are positioned
Output: tools/transit_patterns.json

How it's used:

As documentation (what properties does a SelectWidget2 need?)
By the builder library (template factories can load defaults from this file)
As a diff baseline (re-run after re-export to see what changed)
Part 4: Validation Script
File: tools/validate_retool_json.py

Post-generation validation that catches errors before Retool import:

Outer JSON structure valid (uuid, page.data.appState)
appState parses as valid JSON
Root is ["~#iR", ...] record
Plugins iOM exists and is non-empty
At least one Screen and one Frame plugin present
Every widget has a position2 record
Every widget has type, subtype, id, template
No duplicate plugin IDs
Container references point to existing frames
Screen references point to existing screens
Usage: python3 tools/validate_retool_json.py apps/my-app/output.json

